  <other_name type="common_name">Small-leafed montia</other_name>
  <discussion>Montia parvifolia is a variable diploid and tetraploid species. Plants with larger
        flowers, leaves, and seeds have been treated as var. flagellaris (Bongard) C. L. Hitchcock
        or as the separate species M. sweetseri Henderson. Because the complex has not been studied
        using modern methods, and the variation observed in herbarium specimens has no correlated
        geographical base, I adopt the position of K. L. Chambers (1993) and do not recognize the
        two above-mentioned taxa at this time. I equate the species situation here to that of M.
        fontana and choose not to recognize infraspecific taxa.</discussion>
